    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        public static java.lang.String getValue(java.lang.String key,
                                        java.lang.String baseName,
                                        java.lang.String l10n)
        Returns the value corresponding to the key in the specified resource package and localization. Specified resource package should exist. Also key from the parameter should exist in specified base. On the other hand, if there is no language as in l10n parameter then default locale is used.
        Parameters:
        key - key corresponding to the wanted value.
        baseName - resource package name
        l10n - needed localization
        Returns:
        value corresponding to the specified key

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Obtains command from the console and prints the value corresponding to the parameters of command. Command consists of two words separated with whitespace. First one corresponds to the key, and the second one - to the language. E.g. command "table en" contains key "table" and locale "en". So that's why value "table" can be expected in the result. Any other format of command or unacceptable values will cause a message "Bad format". Application will work untill the EOI will be received.
        Parameters:
        args - command line parameters
